OL,3,CNo pardon for Guernsey policemen sent
OL,4,Cto WW2 labour camps
OL,6,FGuernsey States say they will not
OL,7,Fofficially pardon the policemen who
OL,8,Fwere deported or sent to forced labour
OL,9,Fcamps during the occupation for crimes
OL,10,Fagainst the Nazis.
OL,12,FThe Royal Court convicted 17 policemen
OL,13,Ffor theft and receiving stolen goods
OL,14,Fafter stealing food from the Germans
OL,15,Fto feed hungry islanders.
OL,17,FTheir families had remained hopeful
OL,18,Fthat the States would clear them of
OL,19,Ftheir crimes and grant posthumous
OL,20,Fpardons ahead of the 80th anniversary
OL,21,Fof the Liberation.
