OL,6,FFormer policeman, Fred Duquemin's
OL,7,Fwartime conviction cost him his job
OL,8,Fand his pension.
OL,10,FHis daughter, Rose Short told ITV
OL,11,FNews: "Ironically my widowed mother
OL,12,Freceived two thousand three hundred
OL,13,Fpounds in compensation in 1964 from
OL,14,Fthe Germans.
OL,16,F"So the Germans acknowledged that they
OL,17,Fwere victims of Nazi persecution and
OL,18,Fsome of these men who refused to give
OL,19,Fhim his pension and his rights had
OL,20,Fthemselves received some of the goods
OL,21,Fthat they were condemning them for.
